{"raw_text": "Accepted Answer: (0.075, 0.138)\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nExplanation:\n\nFrom the regression in Q7: b1 (slope) \u00bb 0.091. SE(b1) is computed from regression output. 95% CI = b1 \u00b1\n\nt_critical * SE(b1). With df = n-2 = 4, t_critical(0.025, 4) = 2.776. SE(b1) is calculated as sqrt(MSE / SS_xx) where SS_xx = sum(xi - x_mean)^2 \u00bb 759.33. MSE \u00bb 0.11. SE(b1) = sqrt(0.11/759.33) = sqrt(0.000145) = 0.01203. CI = 0.091 \u00b1 2.776*0.01203 = 0.091 \u00b1 0.0334 = (0.057, 0.124). The accepted answer is (0.075, 0.138).\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE DR.SUVITHA CSE DR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nAssignments 7\u201312 | Questions, Options, Answers and Detailed Explanations\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nUnit 7 - Week 7 | Due: 2020-03-18", "tables_html": [], "images_base64": [""]}_source2020 NPTEL DATA ANALYTICS WITH PYTHON.pdfI(0.075, 0.138)\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE\n\nExplanation:\n\nFrom the regression in Q7: b1 (slope) \u00bb 0.091. SE(b1) is computed from regression output. 95% CI = b1 \u00b1\n\nt_critical * SE(b1). With df = n-2 = 4, t_critical(0.025, 4) = 2.776. SE(b1) is calculated as sqrt(MSE / SS_xx) where SS_xx = sum(xi - x_mean)^2 \u00bb 759.33. MSE \u00bb 0.11. SE(b1) = sqrt(0.11/759.33) = sqrt(0.000145) = 0.01203. CI = 0.091 \u00b1 2.776*0.01203 = 0.091 \u00b1 0.0334 = (0.057, 0.124). The accepted answer is (0.075, 0.138).\n\nDR.SUVITHA CSE